##Joint efforts to fight the epidemic: Beijing, Shanghai and other places to bail out small and medium-sized enterprises, the effectiveness of the implementation of policies

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The introduction of support policies around the more important is to release a signal that the fight against the epidemic is a matter for the whole society. The epidemic situation directly damages the interests of enterprises and social stability, so we should find a feasible way to share the losses

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Zhang Wei and Yu Yan, CAIJING reporters

Editor | Yuen Man

"We received four phone calls today, all of them to help us solve our financial problems, " said Wang Gang, chairman of Dongpo, Meizhou, after nearly half a month of tight funding.

On Feb. 3, Beijing issued the People's Government of Beijing Municipality on measures to further support the fight against COVID-19 pneumonia, the measures include 19 measures to encourage small and medium-sized micro-and micro-tenants to reduce rents moderately and to solve the financing problems of enterprises in difficulty (referred to as "Beijing anti-epidemic 19" for short) .

It's the same thing. On the same day, Shanghai introduced a "burden reduction" policy for enterprises, involving the stability of posts, social security contributions, training subsidies and other aspects. Before that, on February 2, the "ten policy opinions of the People's Government of Suzhou City on responding to the epidemic of pneumonia caused by COVID-19 infection and supporting small and medium-sized enterprises to tide over the difficulties" (hereinafter referred to as "Su 'Hui" ten policies) has also been promulgated, covering aspects such as increasing financial support, stabilizing the workforce and reducing the burden on enterprises.

Since the spread of COVID-19 pneumonia ("new pneumonia") , catering, tourism, film, transportation, education and training industries have been hit, in the industry of small and medium-sized micro-entrepreneurs, self-employed households also face many challenges. (see CAIJING's article, "the epidemic weighs heavily on small and medium-sized enterprises: cash flow is in short supply, lay-offs and layoffs await support" .)

In this context, the industry practitioners, scholars and other sound, call attention to the impact of the epidemic of small and medium-sized enterprises. Industry insiders said that Beijing, Shanghai and Suzhou have introduced relief measures for small and medium-sized enterprises, is a positive response to the current market voice, but the specific effectiveness depends on how the implementation. In addition, to curb the development of the epidemic, so that enterprises as soon as possible to resume production operations, is the fundamental solution to the problem.

Three bail-outs

Wang Gang hasn't had a chance to read the details of "Beijing's 19 anti-epidemic measures, " but he senses a change: On February 3rd, he has received four phone calls from the relevant person in charge of the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Commerce, the person in charge of a commercial bank, the person in charge of a financing and guarantee company, etc. . The other party has learned in detail about the specific problems in Dongpo, Meizhou, some of these institutions have offered to provide financial support.

"This is the best news I've heard in so many days, " Wang Gang told Caijing, adding that after the outbreak, many catering companies were forced to suspend operations, with the attendant problems of rent and personnel costs, become the "big mountain" that presses on them.

Now, these problems are likely to be solved. The reporter from Caijing noted that in terms of stabilizing posts and holding over payment of social insurance, su "Hui" ten proposed that "for the insured enterprises that do not lay off workers or make fewer lay-offs, they can return 50% of the unemployment insurance premiums actually paid in the previous year" , "for small and medium-sized enterprises that are affected by the epidemic and face temporary difficulties in production and operation, and indeed can not afford to pay social insurance premiums in full, they can defer payment of old-age insurance, unemployment insurance and industrial injury insurance premiums for a maximum period of six months after approval according to regulations" , etc. .

The Shanghai municipal government said it would continue to pay 50 percent of the total amount of unemployment insurance premiums actually paid by employers and their employees in the previous year without laying off or reducing employees, and eligible employers would return 50 percent of the total amount of unemployment insurance premiums paid by their employees in the previous year, from this year, the starting and ending date of Shanghai employee social insurance payment year including employee medical insurance year will be adjusted to July 1 of that year to June 30 of the following year, 3 months later. It is estimated that this measure will reduce the social security contribution burden of 10.1 billion yuan for Shanghai enterprises in the current year. In addition, the social insurance payment period was extended, it pointed out that the insured units late payment of social insurance premiums, the relevant procedures can be completed within 3 months after the lifting of the epidemic.

"Beijing anti-epidemic 19" also proposed that enterprises affected by the epidemic, resulting in production and management difficulties, can be adopted by consensus with the staff and workers to adjust pay, rotation, shorten working hours, waiting for a job and other ways to stabilize jobs. Try Not to lay off or reduce the number of employees. Eligible Enterprises May, in accordance with the relevant provisions, refund unemployment insurance premiums.

Meanwhile, the collection period of social insurance premiums payable in January and February will be extended to the end of March. For enterprises in the tourism, accommodation, catering, convention and exhibition, Commerce and Trade Circulation, transportation, education and training, cultural performances, Film and Television Theaters, ice and snow sports and other industries that are seriously affected, the collection period of social insurance premiums payable during the outbreak period may be extended to the end of July.

"Of these policies, the extension of social security is the most valuable to me. Because of the extension of social security, it is equivalent to getting at least several tens of thousands of yuan of circulating funds every month, and one hundred thousand yuan every six months. The more people there are, the more obvious the effect is,"a small and micro business owner told CAIJING.

There are also private enterprises to "finance and Economics" reporters, Beijing this time put forward "with the staff and workers to take measures to adjust pay, " and so on, giving enterprise leaders full autonomy and communication space. Rather than a one-size-fits-all approach that requires companies to pay full salaries to employees even when they have no revenue.

It is worth noting that "Beijing anti-epidemic 19" , Su "Guo" all proposed to encourage the reduction of rent and other measures. The latter also proposes measures such as reducing or exempting small and medium-sized enterprises from taxes and fees and deferring the payment of taxes. "If, due to the epidemic situation, the enterprises have incurred heavy losses and their normal production and business operations have been seriously affected, if it is really difficult to pay the property tax or the urban land use tax, they may apply for a reduction or exemption from the property tax or the urban land use tax; for Small and medium-sized enterprises affected by the epidemic, the enterprises shall apply for an extension of their declaration in accordance with the law. If an enterprise has special difficulties and is unable to pay taxes on time, the enterprise shall apply for an extension of the payment of taxes for a maximum period of three months."

"At present, the most critical issue for the survival of small and micro enterprises is to have sufficient cash flow and to reduce or waive rent. If we pay monthly, it will still have an impact, but we all pay on an annual basis. We have already paid our contributions, so the impact can not be reflected at all. " The above-mentioned owners of small and Micro Enterprises said bluntly, the most important thing right now is to make sure we have enough money.

Wang Gang agrees, telling CAIJING that as long as banks keep lending, stop pumping, and are willing to offer lower interest rates, Dongpo will continue to do so.

CAIJING reporter noted that "Beijing anti-epidemic 19" and Su "Hui" 10 all mentioned increasing financial support for enterprises, and stressed that "affected by the epidemic operating temporary difficulties but prospects for the development of enterprises do not borrow, continue to loan, not pressure loans. ".

Among them, "Beijing anti-epidemic 19" proposed, to guide the financial institutions within the jurisdiction to provide special credit services to enterprises involved in epidemic prevention and control, manufacturing and purchasing of pharmaceutical products, construction of public health infrastructure, scientific research and tackling key problems, etc. , enterprises involved in the epidemic prevention and control of credit applications "special handling. ".

Su's ten-point proposal further states that banks should be encouraged to increase their support for small and micro enterprises by lowering their cost and fee rates, especially for small and micro enterprises in the "three must be one important" key areas and those with financial difficulties, at the same time, if the loan interest rate is lowered to ensure that the loan interest rate is lower than the quoted interest rate in the loan market for the same period, and if the loan interest rate is included in the list of key enterprises of the relevant departments, such as Gongxin, it will be lowered by more than 30% on this basis.

Effectiveness depends on policy implementation

For the Shanghai, Suzhou, Beijing three relief policies, many enterprises believe that the current problem to a certain extent, but overall, I am afraid that the effectiveness is limited.

Xue Hongyan, assistant director of the SUNING Financial Research Institute, said that the support policy, which focuses on tax and fee reduction and financial support, is an active policy within the scope allowed by the policy and can effectively improve the operating difficulties of small and medium-sized enterprises, but the shock mainly comes from the market demand contraction, through the industrial chain upper and lower levels of transmission, interlocking, policy has made positive efforts, but the degree of mitigation is limited.

On the one hand, there are a few companies that can actually get bank funding. The head of a private enterprise said bluntly that from the current Suzhou, Beijing mentioned the bail-out industry, Relatively Limited, and the bank in the specific implementation must also consider a number of factors. It is not easy for companies to actually get loans to solve their current funding problems.

On the other hand, the root cause of the current difficulties is that many enterprises can not return to normal production and operation. "The policies in Beijing, Shanghai and Jiangsu are more from the perspective of government officials and do little to really address the needs of the corporate sector. For the manufacturing industry, the key is to resume work, which is not only the need for enterprises to save themselves, but also the need for the protection of anti-epidemic materials,"Wu Jianming, president of Wanyang Group Co. , Ltd. , told CAIJING, general Manufacturing industrial enterprises before the 20th of the 12th of the 12th month, which means that the material reserves have been consumed for more than 20 days, from anti-epidemic protection materials to animal feed, there have been signs of material shortages. If it spreads, the consequences will be unimaginable and need to be dealt with early.

"In fact, the significance of the support policies is not limited to the support itself, but more importantly, it is to send a signal that the fight against the pneumonia epidemic is a matter for the whole society. The losses caused by the epidemic directly affect enterprises, but the whole society is looking for a feasible way to share the losses, " Xue said.

Pu Zhenxing, a senior economist at the China Post and savings bank, told Caijing that the main difficulty at present is how to resume enterprise production. For some manufacturing enterprises, non-personnel-intensive enterprises should take measures to gradually resume production. And the policy focuses on implementation, only implementation can really ease the difficulties of small and medium-sized enterprises.

It is worth noting that in implementing the relevant policies on financial support, many bankers believe that the requirements of the ten articles of the Su "Hui" that "the interest rate of loans should be increased or decreased by more than 10% " and "the interest rate on loans should be lowered by more than 30% on this basis" , there's something wrong with it.

"It's beyond the purview of local governments and it's hard to really implement. Even the Central Bank, through open-market operations (such as the 10 basis points cut in the reverse repo winning bid on Feb. 3) and MLF-LPR-lending rates, is directing banks to lower financing costs for the real economy, rather than directly asking them to lower lending rates for certain companies,"said one banking researcher.

A senior figure in the financial industry also said that similar measures to support smes had been adopted by local governments in the past. However, the success of these measures would depend on the effectiveness of communication between local governments and banks. Especially in the bank loan pricing mechanism has changed circumstances, it is difficult to say whether it is practical.

Che Ning, Deputy Secretary-general of the Beijing Internet Law Society, told Caijing that it is very valuable to issue such targeted and systematic policy documents under such pressure and in such a short period of time. The problem, however, is in the way it is implemented. With regard to lending rates, first of all, financial supervision, especially of banks, belongs to the Central Government; Second, banks are no longer the "Second Finance" in the era of planned economy, and the pricing mechanism of credit also depends on the market; third, credit policies are mostly concentrated in the headquarters of financial institutions, and local branches can only be reflected to higher authorities and can not make their own decisions. This to a large extent weakened the seriousness of the document, scientific and enforceable.

The financial industry veterans fear that banks may be reluctant to put their money into interest rate depressions because of internal transfer pricing problems. On the other hand, it will result in usurious loans, but harm the enterprise. Perhaps the more feasible and effective measure is a fiscal discount.

Xu Xiaonian, a professor at China Europe International Business School, told the Beijing News in a recent interview that there is still room for fiscal policy to be adjusted by cutting spending rather than raising the deficit. It is suggested that reference should be made to a series of tax reduction and fee reduction policies adopted by the government in 2003 when "SARS" occurred, so as to help enterprises tide over the difficulties.

According to Wu Jianming, the government can support the enterprises in the following ways: extending the loan period and granting discount interest for the epidemic period; confirming the claims for the epidemic period according to the force majeure; following Singapore's practice, providing employment subsidies during the epidemic period; and ensuring the supply of materials by resuming work as soon as possible, relieve pressure on the business. A person in charge of a restaurant company in Beijing said he hoped that the next step would be to consider reducing or waiving the payroll tax for employees.

"As the epidemic has a greater impact on the local tax base, it is suggested that the central government should also strengthen the transfer payments to the local governments, especially those with a greater economic impact, to ensure that the level of local public service provision is not lowered due to the epidemic, and even to the extent that revenues are depleted, fish will be killed and eggs will be killed, " Che said.
